      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      5.0 out of 5 stars Surprisingly these just work
      Reviewed in the United States on April 11, 2020
      Size: 1 Fl Oz (Pack of 1)Verified Purchase
      I'm actually a bit surprised, because the amount you actually give to your baby seems too small to be effective. But you know what? It seems to do the job. We've tried feeding out boy without using these and he does seem fussier, especially if we skip two doses. These are a necessity before a bedtime feeding. They genuinely make him less gassy. They aren't a magic bullet and sometimes his tummy just aches no matter what, but it still is worth using because it cuts his comfort down drastically, and even when he goes get gassy, its much more of a reduced incident.

      In my opinion, get these dye free ones over the red dyed formula, just for the reason that the applicator syringe is different in both, but I like the one in here better. Its a small thing, but when you have a hungry baby screaming, and you just want to get the bottle in their mouth quickly, the syringe in this one is much easier to read and use. It seems confusing at first, but you read the volume at the top as you draw in the fluid. The reason this is better is because the fluid doesn't obscure the numbers. In the original dyed formula, the syringe uses the traditional method of numbers on the syringe body (for some reason) and the liquid makes the numbers hard to read. Why do they even need to make a dyed version anyway? So in my opinion, stick with this version, if supplies allow it.
